Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:23.853 --> 00:00:26.985
I'm Alex Rigan, president of the Association.

00:00:27.895 --> 00:00:30.119
Good evening, I'm the director, Pierre Louis Felix

00:00:31.231 --> 00:00:38.517
Good evening HaitiXhange, my name is Saint-Juste Naissance, the association advisor. I'm here to give all the guys advice.

00:00:39.434 --> 00:00:43.411
How did this association start?

00:00:43.965 --> 00:00:54.447
This was how we started. While I was in communications school, I met a professor named Jack Maurus.

00:00:55.038 --> 00:01:03.480
He told me I had to write a screenplay. Since I had a story, I turned it into a screenplay.

00:01:03.916 --> 00:01:14.325
Then I asked him about promotions, and he told me that to get the word out I would need an association. This was why I started this association.

00:01:14.744 --> 00:01:18.598
What projects have you already worked on?

00:01:19.139 --> 00:01:24.061
Our first project was "Anneau du Ciecle", which failed because of the earthquake. 

00:01:24.430 --> 00:01:33.602
Afterwards we weren't discouraged because we had a very well determined objective, and I surrounded myself with the people you see here, and we did "Fixation".

00:01:33.713 --> 00:01:38.205
Explain the plot of the film "Fixation".

00:01:40.761 --> 00:01:51.025
Yes I wrote it. I can say it is my story, because it's something I experienced. Two young people growing up in a neighborhood. But their families are different. 

00:01:51.930 --> 00:01:57.337
One comes from a lower class, and the other one comes from a class that is a little higher. 

00:01:57.521 --> 00:02:10.235
But they have come to love each other, but the girl's mother does not accept the young man because of his terrible situation.

00:02:10.632 --> 00:02:16.562
After a while the young man does not let life discourage him since he has a well planned objective. 

00:02:17.401 --> 00:02:22.878
I think that even the name of the film explains that it is a 'Fixation'. It is the objective of the person. What they are 'fixated' with in life.

00:02:23.457 --> 00:02:25.835
Can you give us a little scene?

00:02:26.026 --> 00:02:32.633
I'll give you a scene with two people to see what kind of performances they give.

00:02:33.095 --> 00:02:36.343
Good evening, Bernard Marie Beatrice.

00:02:36.731 --> 00:02:41.683
Good evening HaitiXchange, my name is Cadet Lensey and I'm a member of the association.

00:02:42.183 --> 00:02:44.183
Action

00:02:44.948 --> 00:02:52.298
You've asked me to come here, you know I can't stay too long. So tell me what's important so I can leave, because you know I've been grounded.

00:02:54.399 --> 00:03:02.392
The reason I've asked you here, is to explain something to you that has been tormenting me. 

00:03:03.574 --> 00:03:16.062
